    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.9.21-23_0001" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">21</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Hotel La Salle Building</figDesc>
                        <p>La Salle at Madison St.</p>
                    </figure>
                    
                    Hotel La Salle
                        <lb/>
                    Chicago April 26 1922
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute> 
                </opener>
                <p>In the whirl of many things I hope I never forget you.</p> 
                
                <p>I want to thank you for that grand letter and coming from a man like you.</p>
                
                <p>Had a fine talk with Carl Sandberg &#8212; and three hours with Sherwood Anderson and Ben <unclear>Hecht</unclear>.</p> 
                
                <p>Same day &#8212; when the
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.9.21-23_0002"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">22</fw>
                    
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Hotel La Salle Building</figDesc>
                        <p>La Salle at Madison St.</p>
                    </figure>
                    
                    Hotel La Salle
                    <lb/>
                    Chicago_______  192____
                </fw>             
                
                    flurry of snow has settled I shall write you a real letter and tell you all about my <unclear>experiments</unclear>. I <hi rend="underline">promise</hi> you that I shall remain unspoiled.</p> 
                
                <p>I left orders with our Harcourt to send me your review in the <hi rend="caps">M.J.</hi></p>
                
                <p>I was at a luncheon of the <unclear>Bookfellows</unclear> when your telegram to <unclear>Elwin Markhaw</unclear> was read &#8212; and <unclear>it</unclear> pleased all &#8212; and the good <unclear>young</unclear> man in particular.</p> 
                <closer>    
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Jim Tally,</signed>
                    West 47th st, New York
                
                    <note place="left margin" type="authorial"><unclear>c/o ms. Harcourt</unclear></note>
                    
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.9.21-23_0003"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">23</fw>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    <hi rend="caps">MOFFAT YARD &amp; COMPANY
                        <lb/>
                    PUBLISHERS
                        <lb/>
                    31 UNION SQUARE WEST
                        <lb/>
                    NEW YORK</hi>
                </ab>
                
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>A hand, pointing</figDesc>
                    <p>RETURNED TO WRITER.</p>
                </figure>
                
            </div1>
